// CodeMirrorWrapper
// React wrapper around a CodeMirror 6 editor instance.
// Manages editor lifecycle, language mode, theme (light/dark), keymaps,
// annotation decorations, and read-only state. Exposes a ref API for external
// control (getSelection, replaceSelection, getContent).

The editor is initialized once on mount. Content changes are applied via
EditorView.dispatch when the content prop changes externally, avoiding
re-rendering loops by comparing against the current doc string.

Annotations are rendered as colored dot widgets at the start of annotated lines
via a CodeMirror StateField and decoration set.

FUNCTION CodeMirrorWrapper(content, onChange, language, readOnly, annotations, onAnnotationClick, ...) -> JSX  EXPORT
  Creates CodeMirror EditorView with appropriate language extension (mermaid,
  markdown, json, yaml, typescript, or plain text), theme (One Dark or default
  light), standard keymaps, and annotation decoration extension.
  Calls onChange when the document changes.
  Syncs content prop to editor when it changes externally.
  Exposes getSelection / replaceSelection / getContent via forwardRef.
